Treat an existing shared OTP installation directory as normal lock contention.

maybe_install_erlang uses atomic mkdir as a cross-action installation lock. Losing that race is
expected and correctly skips extraction, but plain mkdir also emits a misleading error on stderr.
Silence only that lock-acquisition attempt; real extraction failures remain visible and fatal under
the caller's `set -e`. B3 patch-in-place.

--- a/tools/erlang_toolchain.bzl
+++ b/tools/erlang_toolchain.bzl
@@ -62 +62 @@
-if mkdir "{install_path}"; then
+if mkdir "{install_path}" 2>/dev/null; then
